cs.AR, cs.DS, cs.ET, cs.PL, cs.SE

Reasoning: 

- cs.AR (Architecture): The paper proposes a new architecture/methodology for FPGAs to make them suitable for integer as well as variable precision floating point multiplication. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper may involve the development of new algorithms for performing integer and variable precision floating point multiplication. 
- cs.ET (Embedded Systems): The proposed architecture/methodology may be useful for embedded systems that require efficient variable precision floating point multiplication, such as multimedia processing applications. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages): The paper may involve the development of new programming languages or tools for implementing the proposed architecture/methodology. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper may involve the development of software tools or methodologies for designing and implementing the proposed architecture/methodology.
